step_data.thought:
The previous attempt to click on a map tile failed because there appears to be an overlay element intercepting the pointer events. The error message specifically mentions a 'leaflet-interactive' path element in the 'leaflet-overlay-pane' that's intercepting the clicks.

Looking at the coordinates in the textboxes (elements 505-509), I can see the current export area is defined by coordinates: North (48.587), West (-77.388), East (-65.127), and South (35.224).

To manually select a different area, I should try modifying these coordinate values directly in the textboxes rather than trying to click and drag on the map. I'll focus on one of the coordinate input fields (like the North coordinate) and change its value to define a smaller area. This should help address the issue that the current area is too large to export.

I'll start by clearing and modifying the North coordinate (element 505) to a smaller value.
